<title>NIGERIA: Nigerian 1997 fiscal budget statistics.</title>
<headline>Nigerian 1997 fiscal budget statistics.</headline>
<dateline>LAGOS 1997-01-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Statistics from Nigeria's 1997 fiscal budget. (In naira unless otherwise stated).</p>
<p>		    1995	1996	1997 projection</p>
<p>Inflation rate</p>
<p>   (pct)	  72.8	28.0	 15.0</p>
<p>GDP (pct)	  2.2	 3.25	 5.5</p>
<p>Surplus (bln)    1.0	37.0	Not given</p>
<p>External reserve</p>
<p>   (bln)	   1.441     4.086    Not given</p>
<p>Oil revenue</p>
<p>(blns of dollars)   7.899    10.891     11.045</p>
<p>Non-oil rev(bln)81	 108	  161</p>
<p>Recurrent expenditure</p>
<p>   (bln)	  66	  79	   99</p>
<p>Capital expenditure</p>
<p>    (bln)	 44.0	51.0	 89.0</p>
<p>External debt</p>
<p> (blns of dlars)32.6	28.0	Not given</p>
<p>Source: Nigerian Ministry of Finance.</p>
<p>** Note: Nigeria has two exchange rates, a rate of 22 naira to the dollar for official transactions, and a rate of 80 naira to the dollar for all other transactions.</p>
</text>
